          "Logan Boese"
        ],
        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "Who they were in Life isn't important anymore, they're far enough away from everything they ever knew for it to no longer matter. When they were at the very end of their rope, someone approached them, offering them a fresh start in the military. Nothing to lose, they accepted, and went through basic, finally feeling some purpose to their life, excelling enough to draw the notice of some \"Higher Ups\" To pull them aside. They offered them a chance to be Stronger, Faster, and Tougher than they'd ever dreamed, and all they'd have to do is to continue to serve their country. They agreed and were taken to a facility where they were put through an Experimental Procedure that brought them to the brink of death, before they were given a \"Life-Changing Serum.\" In reality, they were taken control of by an \"Organization\" (Known to Some by a very different name,) that claimed to be the Military and Artificially Embraced with Captured Vitae as part of a process designed to test the limits of Vampire Physiology. They were fed drugs to keep them sedate and compliant as they were put through their paces. Exercises, more Experiments, limited field deployment under controlled circumstances, all of it to see what they were capable of and if they could be expected to stand up to a \"Natural\" Vampire, testing the viability of their condition for military applications and infiltration purposes. Finally, they were deployed to a city controlled by the Sabbat, with the intent of infiltrating it and feeding information back to their masters. This is when they escaped their creators they slipped away from those watching, and escaped into the population in the city. Their Creators had not known that the drugs they'd been fed had never truly been effective, they just had the intelligence to realize they'd been lied to, and to know that they had to feign obedience and to wait for the correct moment to make good their escape. Ever Since, they've been looking over their shoulders, trying to stay one step ahead of being recaptured, and offering their services to the highest bidder. They've come to LA to offer their services to Help, following the... Trouble in the rest of the Vampire world. They recognize the hand of their former masters in recent events, and know that they're close, and they worry that this is the Safest Place they can find. They're terrified that the events of their Embrace will somehow become public, and are willing to play by the Camarilla's (To them, Over-Complex,) Rules to stay alive."
        ],
